description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cambridge University Hospitals (CUH) NHS Foundation Trust comprises Addenbrooke’s Hospital and the Rosie Hospital in Cambridge. With over 11000 staff and over 1100 beds the priorities of the Trust focus on a quality service which is all about people – patients, staff and partners. Recognised as providing ‘outstanding’ care to our patients and rated ‘Good’ overall by the Care Quality Commissioner, is testament to the skill and dedication of the people who work here. CUH’s values – Together- safe, kind, excellent – are at the heart of patient care, defining the way all staff work and behave. The Trust provides accessible high-quality healthcare for the local people of Cambridge, together with specialist services, dealing with rare or complex conditions for a regional, national and international population.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is an exciting new opportunity for a highly talented and committed Operational Manager to help implement and deliver the newly commissioned Paediatric and Neonatal Decision Support and Retrieval Service (PaNDR) service alongside the Clinical Director and ADO. This new service is combining the already established ANTS (Acute Neonatal Transfer Service) with acute Paediatric retrievals from across Norfolk, Suffolk and Cambridgeshire.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This new post will ensure the transition and safe delivery of care to both Neonatal and Paediatric critically ill children from across the East of England to other quaternary centres, should this be required. You will be responsible alongside the CD to ensure robust safety and governance processes are embedded in this new service.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You should have a proven record in operational management in a health setting with strong transferable managerial skills. You will be required to work as part of the MDT, including the Consultant, Nursing and Administrative teams providing strong leadership and managerial support. There will also be the opportunity to work with senior leaders within the NHSE and the wider Trust.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will be expected to support the procurement of new vehicles, supporting the ADO and CD during the tender process. You will also skillfully manage a large budget and human resources to ensure value for money is achieved.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will be integral to the development of a successful, high performing and innovative service with service users at its core.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This vacancy will close on: - 12 November 2020 midnight&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is subject to a satisfactory DBS clearance and as a result, you will be required to pay the associated fee of £40.00. This fee will be deducted from your second month’s salary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits to you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer development opportunities and a wide range of benefits including on-site leisure facilities, shopping concourse, day nurseries and access to a great transport system with easy access to airports and rail travel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details of our fantastic benefits please refer to the attachment below - CUH Benefits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note if you would like to discuss the required hours of this role further, you should approach the contact given. In some cases alternative working hours will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome applications from the Armed Forces.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
